# KCP Protocol & Message Routing

## Transport
- UDP via KCP library (`Plugins/kcp/KCP/`)
- Default server: `127.0.0.1:3250` (Go kcp-server)
- Framing: `[Type(1) | BodyLen(3) | Body(N)]`

## Packet Types
| Type | Name           | Direction      |
|------|----------------|----------------|
| 1    | Handshake      | Both           |
| 2    | HandshakeAck   | Client→Server  |
| 3    | Heartbeat      | Both (every 5s)|
| 4    | Data           | Both           |
| 5    | Kick           | Server→Client  |

## Data Message Format (Pitaya/Pomelo)
Flag byte encodes message type: `msgType = (flag >> 1) & 0x07`

| msgType | Name     | Format                                           |
|---------|----------|--------------------------------------------------|
| 0       | Request  | `[Flag(1)] [ReqID(VarInt)] [RouteLen(1)] [Route] [Body]` |
| 1       | Notify   | `[Flag(0x02)] [RouteLen(1)] [Route] [Body]`      |
| 2       | Response | `[Flag(1)] [ReqID(VarInt)] [Body]`               |
| 3       | Push     | `[Flag(1)] [RouteLen(1)] [Route] [Body]`         |

## Routes

### Client → Server
| Route          | Proto Message  | Type    | Purpose         |
|----------------|---------------|---------|-----------------|
| `room.join`    | JoinRequest   | Request | Join a room     |
| `room.move`    | MoveRequest   | Notify  | Sync position   |
| `room.message` | ChatMessage   | Request | Send chat       |

### Server → Client (Push)
| Route              | Proto Message    | Purpose                   |
|--------------------|-----------------|---------------------------|
| `OnSelfJoin`       | PlayerState     | Confirm join, get own ID  |
| `OnPlayerMove`     | PlayerMovePush  | Other player moved        |
| `OnPlayerJoin`     | PlayerJoinPush  | Player entered room       |
| `OnPlayerLeave`    | PlayerLeavePush | Player left room          |
| `OnPlayerEnterAOI` | PlayerState     | Player entered view range |
| `OnPlayerLeaveAOI` | PlayerLeavePush | Player left view range    |

## Proto Source
Single source of truth: `kcp-server/protocol/game.proto`
Generated C# code: `Assets/Scripts/Protocol/Game.cs`

## Adding New Messages
1. Edit `kcp-server/protocol/game.proto`
2. Run `make proto` in kcp-server (generates both Go and C#)
3. Register handler: `kcpClient.RegisterHandler("RouteName", data => { ... })`
4. For requests with expected responses, use: `kcpClient.SendRequest("route", msg, responseBytes => { ... })`
